text: Mamostong Kangri is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Jammu and Kashmir. This region is disputed. While under control of India, it is also claimed by Pakistan. The mountain is also known as K35 and Mamostang Kangri. It is the 48th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were N. Yamada, K. Yoshida, R. Sharma, P. Das, and H. Chauhan, in 1984. ==References== Category:Karakoram Category:Jammu and Kashmir Category:Mountains of India
